dsDescriptionValue.value:
The Regional Manifestos Project is an ambitious, long-term project, conceived to serve as a comparative cross-country endeavour. The funding obtained so far has allowed us to complete two waves of regional elections in Spain, 2004-2007* and 2008-2011 and we have already started the third one (2012-2016). Moreover, we have recently added the British case (Scotland and Wales). The total number of cases in the dataset is 58 (see the list bellow). The dataset will be periodically updated in order to add new manifestos.


What cases are included?

SPAIN

Andalusia: 2008 (PP y PSOE) y 2012 (PP y PSOE)

Aragon: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Asturias: 2011 (PP y PSOE) 2012 (PP y PSOE)

Balearic Islands: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Canary Islands: 2011 (PP, PSOE y Coalición Canaria)

Cantabria: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Castile-La Mancha: (manifestos not available)

Castile and Leon: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Catalonia: 2010 (PP, PSC y CiU) y 2012 (PP, PSC, CiU, ERC, ICV-EUiA, C's y CUP)

Valencian Community: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Extremadura: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Galicia: 2009 (PP, PSOE y BNG) 2012 (PSOE)

La Rioja: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Madrid: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Navarre: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Basque Country: 2009 (PP, PSE y PNV) y 2012 (PP, PSE, PNV, IU y Bildu)

Murcia: 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Framework manifesto 2011 (PP y PSOE)

Spanish General elections 2011 (PP y PS OE)

Programas Marco Regionales 2011 (PP, PSOE)


UNITED KINDOM

Scottland: 2011 (Scottish Conservative Party, Scottish National Party y Scottish Labour)

Wales: 2011 (Welsh Labour, Welsh Conservative Party y Plaid Cymru)
